Retrochalcones are polyphenolic compounds and thus have the potential to scavenge different reactive species. Recently, we examined the antioxidant potential of echinatin toward eighteen different reactive oxygen species and it was found to effectively scavenge fifteen of the considered eighteen species (
Mittal and Kakkar, 2020
). It follows that the other retrochalcones should also have the potential to scavenge different reactive species. In this regard, we have considered six reactive oxygen and nitrogen species (ROS/RNS) which are known to exert damaging effects in biological systems. The ROS include the hydroxyl and hydroperoxyl radicals, superoxide and carbonate radical anions, and the RNS include the nitrogen monoxide and nitrogen dioxide radicals.

The hydroxyl radical is the most oxidizing ROS and is responsible for the oxidative damage to DNA. The long half-life of the hydroperoxyl radical allows it to reach remote cellular locations. Although the reactivity of the nitric oxide radical is low, its excessive production may lead to cellular damage. It may react with the superoxide radical anion and produce peroxynitrite, which is a powerful oxidizing and nitrating agent, capable of damaging proteins, lipids and DNA (
Ferreira et al., 2018
; 
Galano & Raúl Alvarez-Idaboy, 2019
).

In the present work, we have considered six retrochalcones, 
viz
. echinatin (
1
), licochalcone A (
2
), licochalcone B (
3
), licochalcone C (
4
), licochalcone D (
5
) and licochalcone E (
6
), which differ in the position of three substituents, i.e. 1ˮ,1ˮ-dimethylallyl, 3ˮ-methyl-2ˮ-butenyl (or prenyl) and 1ˮ,2ˮ-dimethyl-2ˮ-propenyl, represented as X, Y and Z, respectively, in addition to the hydroxyl group (
Fig. 1
). The ground state conformations of the compounds (
1–6
) were determined in our previous work, and are shown in 
Fig. 2
(Mittal et al., 2020; 
Mittal and Kakkar, 2021
). All the species in the present work were generated from these most stable conformations of the considered retrochalcones.

